2 Career
3 Personal life
4 Death
5 References



Early life[edit]
William Harding Jackson was born on March 25, 1901 on the Belle Meade Plantation, in Belle Meade, Tennessee near Nashville, Tennessee. His father of the same name was William Harding Jackson (1874-1903), and his mother, Anne Davis Richardson (1877-1954) (later remarried to Maxwell Stevenson of Hempstead, New York).[3]
